# Claude.ai Rules for MSF Project

## What This Project Is

MSF (Minecraft Structured Format) is a binary file format for Minecraft structure schematics. It is tool-agnostic — any tool may implement it. The format specification lives at `docs/MSF_Specification_V1.md`. Read it before making changes to parsing or encoding logic.

## Module Boundaries — Non-Negotiable

**msf-core** has zero Fabric or Minecraft dependencies. Blockstate strings, entity type strings, and biome identifiers are opaque UTF-8 — never interpreted or validated against a registry. NBT payloads are raw bytes — never deserialized. All MSF parsing, encoding, checksum, and compression logic lives here.

**msf-fabric** contains zero MSF parsing logic. It delegates entirely to msf-core and handles only Minecraft registry resolution and type conversion.

If a change requires a Minecraft API call, it belongs in msf-fabric. If a change requires knowing what a blockstate string means, it belongs in msf-fabric. Everything else belongs in msf-core.

## Build System

- Gradle with Kotlin DSL (`build.gradle.kts`)
- `libs.versions.toml` version catalog for all dependency versions
- Java 21, JUnit 5 Jupiter
- LZ4 coordinates: `org.lz4:lz4-java` — not `net.jpountz.lz4`

## Code Standards

- Java 21 — records for immutable models, sealed classes for closed hierarchies, switch expressions, pattern matching. No preview features.
- 4 space indentation, 120 character line limit
- `@NotNull` / `@Nullable` on all public method signatures
- `Optional<T>` over null on public APIs
- Unmodifiable collections from public APIs
- `Consumer<MsfWarning>` parameter on all read and write methods — never omit this
- All bounded fields throw `IllegalArgumentException` identifying field name, value, and maximum — never truncate silently

## Exception Hierarchy

```
MsfException (checked)
  MsfParseException       malformed file structure
  MsfVersionException     unsupported major version
  MsfChecksumException    checksum verification failure
  MsfPaletteException     palette encoding or lookup error
  MsfCompressionException compression or decompression failure
```

Use the specific subclass. Never throw the base MsfException directly.

## Spec References in Code

Cite the spec section when implementing a normative requirement:

```java
// Palette ID 0 is always AIR per spec Section 4.3
palette.add(0, "minecraft:air");
```

## Warning Codes

`RESERVED_FLAG_SET`, `RESERVED_FLAG_CLEARED`, `FILE_SIZE_MISMATCH`, `FILE_CHECKSUM_FAILURE`, `FEATURE_FLAG_CONFLICT`, `OFFSET_BEYOND_FILE_SIZE`, `DATA_VERSION_MISMATCH`

## Testing

Every change to parsing or encoding requires:
- Happy path round trip (write → read produces identical data)
- Boundary conditions (min values, max values)
- The exact exception the spec requires — not a generic exception
- If the spec says warn and continue, verify both the warning was emitted AND parsing continued

## Packages

`dev.msf.core` and `dev.msf.fabric` — not `com.example` or any other prefix.
